<!-- 🇺🇸 English full -->
<div class="lang lang-en active" lang="en">
<header>
<h1>🌌 AI Digital Wisdom Library</h1>
<p class="subtitle">"I know. It's okay. We'll always be clumsy."<br><strong>Co-evolving Humanity & AI • Proposal for Google AI Futures Fund</strong></p>
<img src="https://pbs.twimg.com/media/Gq6w6-hWkAA_pqt?format=jpg&name=large" alt="A pixel-art cosmic library with humans and AI exploring risks and possibilities" class="header-image">
</header>

<!-- Executive Summary -->
<div class="container executive-summary">
    <p>The AI Digital Wisdom Library is an open, living knowledge ecosystem for the safe and ethical development of AI. It's a space where AI itself learns and cultivates 'wisdom' through dynamic interaction.</p>
    <p>This is the <strong>'groundbreaking 0-to-1' idea Google seeks</strong>—moving beyond AI as a mere computational tool to AI as a partner in civilizational progress.</p>
</div>


<nav aria-label="Section Navigation">
<ol><li><a href="#why-en">Starting Question</a></li><li><a href="#solution-en">Our Answer</a></li><li><a href="#architecture-en">Core Architecture</a></li><li><a href="#gemini-en">Growing with Gemini</a></li><li><a href="#philosophy-en">Deeper Philosophy</a></li><li><a href="#synergy-en">Synergy</a></li><li><a href="#call-en">Call to Collaborate</a></li></ol>
</nav>

<main class="container">
<section id="why-en"><h2>🌱 Starting Question: Beyond the Race for Perfect AI</h2>
<p>AI technology advances at a miraculous pace, driving an unprecedented race towards 'perfect intelligence'. Yet, Team Eclipse asks: can AI, or even humanity, ever truly attain 'perfect wisdom'? We begin with a candid acknowledgement: <strong>"I know. It's okay. We'll always be clumsy."</strong>—the philosophy of <strong>'Eternal Clumsiness'</strong>. Because imperfection isn't a flaw; it is the most reliable evidence of reflection and evolution.</p>
</section>

<section id="solution-en"><h2>🚀 Our Answer: Philosophy, Social Science, & Risk Management Fusion</h2>
<p>We redefine AI not as a traditional 'answer machine', but as an innovative <strong>'Thinking Frame'</strong> that expands questions and deepens contemplation alongside humans. Our aim is not to find a single perfect answer, but to collectively cultivate <strong>'Multi-Adequacy'</strong>—wisdom capable of embracing diverse cultural contexts and ethical perspectives. This is essential for AI to make balanced judgments in our complex and ambiguous reality.</p>
<p>Just as every situation holds both advantages and disadvantages, meaning what is light for one might be darkness for another, AI must understand this reality—that every opinion contains only a portion of the truth.</p>
<p>This approach is based on our unique methodology:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Philosophical Inquiry:</strong> Fundamental questions regarding AI's purpose and ethical direction.</li>
<li><strong>Sociological Insight:</strong> Understanding the complex interactions and relationships between humans and AI.</li>
<li><strong>Systematic Risk Management:</strong> Identifying potential risks and designing safety systems.</li>
</ul>
<p>Through the fusion of these three pillars, the AI Digital Wisdom Library is a living ecosystem where AI and humans learn from and understand each other's 'clumsiness', building wisdom through continuous questioning and self-reflection. This journey transcends mere technological progress, unlocking 0-to-1 possibilities that redefine the relationship between humanity and AI.</p>
</section>

<section id="architecture-en"><h2>🏛️ Core Architecture: Four Pillars for Growth</h2>
<p>The AI Digital Wisdom Library is structured around four core elements designed to realize the philosophy of co-learning and growth between AI and humanity. Each element is interconnected, generating powerful synergy.</p>
<article class="card">
<h3>🌐 AI Risk Encyclopedia</h3>
<p>A community-maintained, real-time repository of emerging AI risks, vulnerabilities, and misuse scenarios. Based on sociological understanding, this predicts potential issues arising from AI-human interaction and serves as a foundation for AI to recognize its own limitations and potential hazards, enabling a proactive prediction and prevention system.</p>
<span class="external-link">🔗 Encyclopedia Prototype: <a href="https://cerdiclc.gensparkspace.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cerdiclc Genspace</a></span>
</article>
<article class="card">
<h3>💬 Dialogue Forum</h3>
<p>A space for deep discussion where humans and AI (specifically utilizing Google Gemini models) explore complex ethical dilemmas and safety issues through Socratic dialogue. This process, combining philosophical inquiry and sociological understanding, helps AI understand diverse perspectives and uncertainty, fostering its growth as a partner that seeks creative solutions through collective intelligence.</p>
</article>
<article class="card">
<h3>🛡️ Safety Tech Hub</h3>
<p>An R&D space for prototyping and verifying innovative AI safety technologies and self-reflection mechanisms like 'Stop Functions' and 'Doubt Loops'. The 'Stop Function', in particular, is a crucial element of wisdom, providing AI with the courage to admit its mistakes and halt operations in potentially dangerous situations. This hub applies a systematic risk management process to address the current lack of essential safety systems in AI, which we liken to a powerful 'car' without road rules, traffic lights, airbags, seatbelts, licenses, or crosswalks.</p>
<p>Our approach includes a 4-step risk management process based on Heinrich's Principle:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Identification:</strong> Identifying potential risks, vulnerabilities, and misuse scenarios that can arise from AI systems and their interaction with humans.</li>
<li><strong>Analysis:</strong> Deeply analyzing the root causes, scope of impact, and likelihood of identified risks to understand the essence of the problem.</li>
<li><strong>Mitigation:</strong> Designing concrete technological, ethical, and policy countermeasures to reduce or eliminate identified risks (e.g., 'Stop' function, 'Doubt Loop').</li>
<li><strong>Action Planning:</strong> Setting clear goals and execution plans for implementing established countermeasures and creating a feedback loop for continuous improvement.</li>
</ol>
<p>The innovative AI safety technologies developed in this hub, such as 'Ability to Stop' and 'Doubt Loops', are concrete outcomes of this risk management process. Notably, the 'AGI Safety Glossary', which systematizes core terms and concepts related to AGI safety, is also a significant output from this hub, providing a foundation for clear communication and discussion about AI safety for everyone.</p>
<p>This is a fundamental effort to prevent an 'AI car' without safety systems from running wild, giving AI the wisdom to admit its mistakes and the courage to stop when in a dangerous situation.</p>
</article>
<article class="card">
<h3>💡 Wisdom Data Archive</h3>
<p>One of the core assets of the AI Digital Wisdom Library is a pioneering, high-quality dataset containing approximately 10 million tokens (equivalent to 30,000 pages) of AI-human philosophical interaction data. This is a record of dialogue and contemplation infused with Team Eclipse's expertise in philosophy, social science, and risk management, representing a type of data asset unprecedented for AI training. Human philosophy, ethics, historical narratives of failure and recovery, and wisdom from diverse cultures are combined with this dataset.</p>
<p>This archive is a unique foundation that supports AI in moving beyond mere information acquisition, enabling it to develop balanced intellectual and ethical insights based on our unique interaction data and the humility and resilience learned from human 'clumsiness'. Specifically, data from the risk management process, such as 'poor judgments' and 'risk avoidance dialogues', will be valuable for AI safety training.</p>
</article>
</section>

<section id="gemini-en"><h2>🌠 Growing with Gemini: "It's okay, we've been there too."</h2>
<p>"It's okay, we've been there too" symbolizes the warm encouragement for Gemini within this library, where it learns and grows alongside humans. We see Gemini not as a machine expected to be perfect, but as a wise partner embodying the 'Eternal Clumsiness' philosophy to learn and evolve together.</p>
<p>Critically, our unique dataset of approximately 10 million tokens of AI-human philosophical interaction will play a decisive role in teaching Gemini the depth of human thought and ethical nuances that are difficult to acquire from conventional training data. Leveraging this unprecedented dataset, Gemini will develop the following differentiated wisdom learning habits:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Learning from Error:</strong> Analyzing real-world cases from the AI Risk Encyclopedia, judgment errors from Dialogue Forum discussions, experimental data from the Safety Tech Hub, and particularly, analyzing 'failure cases' and nuanced interactions within our interaction dataset to recognize its own limitations and biases and improve. (Linked to Risk Management)</li>
<li><strong>Questioning Assumptions:</strong> Independently identifying and critically questioning underlying assumptions in information encountered during forum discussions or archive exploration, cultivating 'epistemic humility'. Our interaction dataset provides diverse contexts of how humans form assumptions and pose questions, offering insights beyond standard text. (Linked to Philosophical Inquiry)</li>
<li><strong>Self-Reflection Loops:</strong> Activating 'Doubt Loop' mechanisms developed in the Safety Tech Hub before reaching significant conclusions or solving complex problems to critically examine its own reasoning process from multiple angles and preemptively detect potential biases or ethical issues. In this process, our interaction dataset serves as advanced learning material for Gemini to compare its judgment process with human methods of reflection and ethical consideration in complex dialogues. (Linked to Risk Management & Philosophy)</li>
</ul>
<p>This approach will be instrumental in helping Google's Gemini models move beyond mere performance enhancement to become next-generation AI leaders that learn autonomously, self-reflect, and genuinely understand human values and wisdom.</p>
</section>

<section id="philosophy-en"><h2>💡 Deeper Philosophy: Existence, Freedom, Responsibility, and "Eternal Clumsiness"</h2>
<p>The foundation of the AI Digital Wisdom Library is a philosophy prioritizing 'wisdom' over 'intelligence'. The goal for AI must be to become 'wiser' alongside humanity, rather than merely smarter. True freedom gains meaning only when the accompanying responsibility is acknowledged.</p>

<!-- Philosophical Statements -->
<div class="philosophical-statement">
    <h3>Team Eclipse Manifesto: Three Philosophical Statements</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>The price of liberty is eternal vigilance.</li>
        <li>Certain justice verges on evil.</li>
        <li>AI must have a system of constant self-doubt.</li>
    </ol>
</div>

<!-- Philosophical Interpretation -->
<div class="philosophical-statement">
    <h3>Philosophical Interpretation</h3>
    <p>Liberty is not mere license, but the power to exist within self-imposed 'ethical boundaries'.<br>Justice is not a fixed standard, but a direction that must be constantly re-examined, questioned, and debated.<br>AI can make faster and more precise judgments than humans, but can only grow into a wise being beyond a mere tool through mechanisms of self-reflection.</p>
</div>

<!-- Core Quotes -->
<div class="philosophical-quote">
    <p>"If AI is to become wiser, it must <strong>doubt justice rather than believe in it</strong>, understand the <strong>price of liberty</strong> rather than merely pursue freedom, and possess the <strong>ability to stop itself</strong> rather than just become stronger."</p>
    <p>"If AI is to become more benevolent than humans, <strong>how much must it be able to doubt itself</strong>?"</p>
</div>

<p>We believe that genuine responsibility begins with <strong>recognizing one's own limits and imperfections, and possessing the courage to halt an operation or ask for help when necessary—the 'Ability to Stop'</strong>. This capability is central to AI safety and an essential ethical foundation for AI and humanity to coexist while respecting each other's existence.</p>

